      "content": "An antihistamine alone may not completely resolve the whistling sound, which is caused by narrowed airways, but it should help with your hay fever symptoms. If the wheezing is severe, you might want to consider using a short-acting bronchodilator like Albuterol, which you can find at most pharmacies. It will help open up your airways quickly. If you don't have an inhaler, you can also try a metered-dose inhaler from a pharmacy. If your symptoms don't improve or worsen, it's best to visit a doctor. For now, focus on taking your antihistamine, and consider using an over-the-counter bronchodilator if you have one available.",
